    "body": "### Fixed\n\n- **`login_anthropic()` ΓÇõ scope set ∞Ùã Hermes ∞ÕÇ 1:1 ∞Ù╝∞╣Ì (`org:create_api_key user:profile user:inference`).**\n  v0.99.7 ∞ÙÌ `claude.ai/oauth/authorize` + `console.anthropic.com`\n  redirect_uri ∞í░φòÒ∞Ù┤ production-tested Hermes φÔ¿φã┤Ω│╝ ∞áòφòÒ∞Ù╕δì░δÂã\n  ∞é¼∞ÜÒ∞₧É ∞Í£δÂã Ω▓░Ω│╝ δÌÉ \"Invalid request format\". dump ∞ÙÌ\n  `authorize_url_full` δ╣ãΩ╡É Ω▓░Ω│╝ single ∞░¿∞Ù┤ = scope. ∞Ü░δª¼Ω░Ç binary\n  ∞ÙÌ hint string (`user:sessions:claude_code`, `user:mcp_servers`)\n  φÂ¼φò¿∞Í£∞╝£ unregistered scope Ω▒░∞áê. Hermes ∞ÙÌ narrower set ∞£╝δí£ ∞óüφ₧Ì\n  (`hermes-agent/agent/anthropic_adapter.py:1044`).\n\n- **`login_anthropic()` ΓÇõ narrowed scope set to Hermes parity.**\n  v0.99.7's authorize + redirect URI parity with Hermes still produced\n  \"Invalid request format\". Diffing dump's `authorize_url_full`\n  against Hermes's URL revealed the single remaining mismatch: scope.\n  Claude Code's binary advertises `user:sessions:claude_code` and\n  `user:mcp_servers` in a hint string, but the OAuth client only\n  accepts the smaller set Hermes ships. Now sending\n  `org:create_api_key user:profile user:inference` exactly."
