    "body": "### Fixed\n\n- **`login_anthropic()` ΓÇõ authorize URL host δ│ÇΩ▓╜ (`platform.claude.com` ΓÁÈ `claude.com/cai`).**\n  v0.99.5 forensic dump Ω░Ç token exchange δÍ¿Ω│ã dump 0Ω▒┤ ΓÇõ ∞é¼∞ÜÒ∞₧É δ│┤Ω│á Ω▓░Ω│╝\n  authorize δÍ¿Ω│ã∞ùÉ∞ã£ \"Invalid Request Format\" Ω▒░∞áê. Claude Code binary ∞ÙÌ\n  authorize URL ∞âÙ∞ã▒ ∞╜õδô£ `O ? CLAUDE_AI_AUTHORIZE_URL : CONSOLE_AUTHORIZE_URL`\n  δ╢ãΩ╕░∞ùÉ∞ã£ ∞Ü░δª¼Ω░Ç φò¡∞âü CONSOLE URL ∞é¼∞ÜÒφò£ Ω▓â∞Ù┤ root cause. Claude Max\n  (consumer) ∞é¼∞ÜÒ∞₧Éδèõ `claude.com/cai/oauth/authorize` Ω░Ç ∞áòδÍ╡.\n  token endpoint (`platform.claude.com/v1/oauth/token`) δèõ Ω╖╕δÔÇδí£ ∞£á∞ºÇ.\n\n- **`login_anthropic()` ΓÇõ switched authorize host from `platform.claude.com`\n  to `claude.com/cai` for Claude.ai consumer accounts.** v0.99.5 forensic\n  dumps showed no `response-*` stages ΓÇõ server-side authorize page\n  rejected the request with \"Invalid Request Format\" before any callback.\n  Claude Code's binary picks one of two authorize hosts via\n  `loginMethod`; we now mirror the Claude Pro / Max consumer branch\n  by default (`claude.com/cai/oauth/authorize`). Token endpoint\n  unchanged."
