    "date": "2026-05-17",
    "body": "### Added\n\n- **`login_anthropic()` ΓÇõ owned-Anthropic OAuth PKCE flow (claude CLI\n  ∞ÙÌ∞í┤∞ã▒ ∞á£Ω▒░).** `/login anthropic` Ω░Ç δìõ ∞Ù┤∞âü `claude /login`\n  subprocess δÑ╝ φÌ╕∞╢£φòÌ∞ºÇ ∞òèΩ│á GEODE Ω░Ç ∞ºü∞áÀ PKCE redirect flow ∞êÌφÚÊ\n  ΓÇõ loopback callback server (δ₧£δìñ free port 54123-54199), PKCE\n  code_verifier/challenge ∞âÙ∞ã▒, `https://platform.claude.com/oauth/\n  authorize` browser open, `https://api.anthropic.com/v1/oauth/token`\n  φÁáφü░ Ω╡ÉφÕÌ, `~/.geode/auth.toml` ∞ÙÌ `providers.anthropic` section ∞ùÉ\n  ∞áÇ∞₧Ñ. multi-candidate client_id ∞Í£δÂã path (`9d1c250a-...` δô▒ reverse-\n  engineered) + first-success-wins. macOS/Linux/Windows δ¬¿δÀÉ δÂÕ∞₧À.\n  `read_geode_anthropic_credentials` φù¼φì╝Ω░Ç `read_geode_openai_\n  credentials` ∞ÕÇ δÂÕ∞Ù╝ shape ∞£╝δí£ δ░ÌφÕÌ. `claude_code_provider.\n  resolve_claude_oauth_token` / `get_claude_oauth_metadata` Ω░Ç auth.\n  toml ∞Ü░∞ãá read + macOS keychain backwards-compat fallback. ToS Tier\n  3 (impersonation) ΓÇõ `claude_code_provider` ∞ÙÌ module docstring ∞ÙÌ\n  policy notice Ω░Ç SOT. failure ∞Í£ graceful fallback (`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n  Ω╢Ô∞₧Ñ message).\n- **`login_anthropic()` ΓÇõ owned-Anthropic OAuth PKCE flow (drops\n  `claude` CLI dependency).** `/login anthropic` no longer spawns\n  `claude /login`; GEODE drives the PKCE redirect flow itself ΓÇõ\n  loopback callback (free port 54123-54199), PKCE\n  `code_verifier`/`challenge` pair, browser open against\n  `platform.claude.com/oauth/authorize`, token exchange at\n  `api.anthropic.com/v1/oauth/token`, persist into\n  `~/.geode/auth.toml` `providers.anthropic`. Multi-candidate\n  `client_id` loop (`9d1c250a-...` first) with first-success-wins.\n  Cross-platform (macOS / Linux / Windows). `read_geode_anthropic_\n  credentials` mirrors the OpenAI helper shape.\n  `claude_code_provider.resolve_claude_oauth_token` and\n  `get_claude_oauth_metadata` now prefer the `auth.toml` source with\n  the macOS keychain kept as a backwards-compat fallback. ToS Tier 3\n  (impersonation) per `claude_code_provider` module docstring;\n  failure surfaces an `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` fallback hint.\n\n\n- **`docs/architecture/provider-login.md` ΓÇõ provider login flow SOT.**\n  OpenAI (device-code) ∞ÕÇ Anthropic (PKCE redirect) ∞ÙÌ OAuth flow ∞ÙÌ\n  ∞áòφòÒ spec ∞ÍáΩ╖£. owned-credential φÔ¿φã┤ (auth.toml SOT + GEODE Ω░Ç ∞ºü∞áÀ\n  OAuth client) ∞ÙÌ architecture + 5-mismatch ∞áòφòÒ plan + ToS Tier\n  spectrum (0-4) ∞áò∞ÙÌ. PR C3 (owned-Anthropic PKCE Ω╡¼φÌã) ∞ÙÌ reference\n  SOT.\n- **`docs/architecture/provider-login.md` ΓÇõ provider login flow SOT.**\n  Architecture spec for the two-provider OAuth picture: OpenAI's\n  device-code flow plus Anthropic's PKCE redirect flow share an\n  owned-credential pattern (auth.toml as SOT, GEODE acts as OAuth\n  client directly). Covers the 5 mismatch points the upcoming PR C3\n  will close and pins down the ToS Tier (0-4) spectrum the choice\n  sits in.\n\n### Removed\n\n- **`/auth` ∞è¼δ₧Ì∞Í£ δ¬àδá╣ ∞Õã∞áã ∞á£Ω▒░ + `/login source` ∞Íá∞ãñ.** `/auth` ∞ÙÌ ∞₧õ∞í┤\n  surface (`add` / `remove` / `set <provider> <source>`) Ω░Ç δ¬¿δÀÉ `/login`\n  ∞£╝δí£ φÙí∞êÌ. `/login source <provider> <type>` ∞ÍáΩ╖£ ΓÇõ Ω╕░∞í┤ `/auth set` ∞ÙÌ\n  credential source picker. `routing.py` ∞ÙÌ `/auth` CommandSpec, `dispatcher.py`\n  ∞ÙÌ cmd_auth dispatch, `core/cli/__init__.py` ∞ÙÌ TTY_LOCAL_COMMANDS ∞ÙÌ\n  `/auth` δÒñδ▓ã, `_state.py` ∞ÙÌ `COMMAND_MAP` ∞ÙÌ `/auth` entry + help line,\n  `commands/__init__.py` ∞ÙÌ export, `core/cli/commands/auth.py` φÔÔ∞Ù╝ ∞₧É∞▓┤\n  δ¬¿δÀÉ ∞á£Ω▒░. `manage_auth` LLM tool ∞ÙÇ backwards-compat adapter δí£ ∞£á∞ºÇ\n  ΓÇõ φÌ╕∞╢£ ∞Í£ `manage_login` δí£ forward (legacy prompts φÌ╕φÕÌ). Plan vs\n  Profile δ╢ãδª¼ ∞ÙÌ historical Ω╖╝Ω▒░ (`PlanRegistry` vs `ProfileStore`) δèõ\n  ∞£á∞ºÇδÉÌδÉÌ, ∞é¼∞ÜÒ∞₧É ∞ºã∞₧à∞áÉ∞ÙÇ `/login` δÍ¿∞Ù╝ SOT.\n- **`/auth` slash command fully removed + `/login source` introduced.**\n  The remaining `/auth` surface (`add` / `remove` / `set <provider>\n  <source>`) was folded into `/login`. The new `/login source <provider>\n  <type>` is the migrated credential-source picker (was `/auth set`,\n  PR #1203). Removed: `routing.py` entry, `dispatcher.py` dispatch +\n  import, `_TTY_LOCAL_COMMANDS` membership, `_state.py` `COMMAND_MAP` +\n  help line, `commands/__init__.py` exports, and the\n  `core/cli/commands/auth.py` source file itself. The `manage_auth`\n  LLM tool is kept as a backwards-compat adapter that forwards to\n  `manage_login` so legacy prompts still work. The underlying Plan vs\n  Profile split (`PlanRegistry` vs `ProfileStore`) is unchanged ΓÇõ only\n  the user-facing entry point is unified."
